title: For Sale:  Italian Bodeo 1889 Made in 1915
postcontent: For sale is an interesting Italian revolver that saw time in several European conflicts. It is a Bodeo 1889 in 10.35 caliber.  The gun has little to no finish remaining with a nice patina. It cycles and functions fine, but I have never fired it.   Made in 1915. Please see pictures for some of the markings and condition. This is an octogon barreled version, which was issued to general enlisted men in the Italian Army. Round barreled versions were for non-com officers. This is the non-folding trigger version, which is rarer than the folding trigger model. These are not an expensive gun, but you rarely come across them (at least I don't see them often.) Will meet in johnson city. Not interested in shipping.  Please email me for pictures.  Here is a description of the history of this model;The Bodeo Model 1889 revolver was invented by Italian firearm designer Carlo Bodeo. Based on the Chamelot-Delvigne Model 1873 revolver, it was produced by a wide variety of manufacturers between 1889 and 1925. It was also produced in Spain from 1915 to 1918. The Bodeo Model 1889 was employed by the Italian Army during World War I, the Interwar Italian colonial wars, and World War II.
